Runtime dependencies (loaded by the user's browser at runtime, not bundled)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

The chess4D-OC application loads the following Python packages from PyPI
into a Pyodide WebAssembly runtime in the user's browser at page load.
The packages are NOT vendored, mirrored, or redistributed by this
repository. The end user's browser fetches them directly from PyPI.

  1. chess-spectral (>= 1.3.0)
     License: GPL-3.0-or-later
     PyPI:    https://pypi.org/project/chess-spectral/
     Source:  https://github.com/lemonforest/chess-spectral

  2. python-chess4d-oana-chiru (>= 0.3.3)
     License: Unlicense (public domain)
     PyPI:    https://pypi.org/project/python-chess4d-oana-chiru/

  3. pyodide
     License: MPL-2.0
     CDN:     https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/pyodide/

  4. three.js (r128)
     License: MIT
     CDN:     https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/three@0.128.0/


Licensing posture: aggregation, not derivative
----------------------------------------------

chess-spectral is GPL-3.0-or-later. This repository's source code does not
incorporate, link against, or redistribute chess-spectral. The combination
of chess-spectral with this MIT-licensed frontend occurs in the end user's
browser at runtime, when the user (or, equivalently, their browser acting
on their behalf) fetches chess-spectral from PyPI via Pyodide's micropip
loader.

This is the same legal posture as an MIT-licensed application that calls
into a GPL system library installed by the user — the works are aggregated
at runtime by the user, not combined into a derivative work by the
distributor of this repository. See:
  - GPL FAQ "What is the difference between an 'aggregate' and other kinds
    of 'modified versions'?"
    https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-faq.html#MereAggregation
  - "Mere aggregation" clause in GPL-3.0 §5

To preserve this posture, contributors to this repository MUST NOT:
  - Vendor, copy, or mirror chess-spectral source or wheels into this repo
  - Bundle chess-spectral into a build artifact distributed from this repo
  - Pre-cache chess-spectral on a CDN controlled by this project's
    maintainers (CDN re-distribution may itself trigger GPL obligations)

The micropip install MUST hit the user's PyPI mirror (typically
pypi.org) at runtime in the user's browser. Loading chess-spectral
from anywhere else converts the runtime aggregation into bundled
distribution and triggers GPL-3.0-or-later for the entire combined work.


Smoke / parity test corpus and research references
--------------------------------------------------

The 4D_CHESS_RESEARCH_PAPER.md in this repository documents the
mathematical framework of the upstream 4d_chess project. The
chess-spectral Phase Operator Supplement (referenced from PR #67 of the
upstream chess-spectral project) underpins the spectral visualization
layer added in M5–M6.
